          {
            "title":"Working with a leader or mentor",
            "body" :"<p>If someone has recommended this study to you — a pastor, a small group leader, or a trusted friend — that relationship matters. 1 John raises personal questions about assurance, love, and what genuine faith looks like in practice. Having someone to think those questions through with can make the difference between the letter producing its intended comfort and it becoming a source of unnecessary anxiety.</p><p>At the end of each chapter, the <b>Share</b> button lets you send your written answers directly to your leader or mentor — via WhatsApp, email, or any other app on your phone. This gives them a window into your thinking before you meet, and makes for a much richer conversation.</p>"
